  "elapsed_s": 316.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The real searches-- I think the first time that they sealed off the Jewish section of Krakow was around December of 1939.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One very early morning, 5 or 6 o'clock, we heard goosestepping.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we looked out the window, and we saw the Germans [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] marching into the section.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And every, let's say, half a block, two soldiers standing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we knew that something is up, but we didn't have the experience yet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And sure enough, then we found out that they're going from home to-- house to house, searching for valuables, for-- looking through the different papers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so we were sitting the house, afraid of what's going to be next.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And sure enough, a German officer with three soldiers walked into the house and asked, bring out all the valuables.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But luckily, my mother had the foresight-- what she did before, because we expected something like that, we had very heavy doors in the apartment.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The doors were about, I would say, probably 2 inches thick.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we knew a carpenter, whom we call.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he made a cavity at the bottom of the doors with a strip of wood that was on two screws.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The doors were taken off the hinges.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In that cavity, my mother was hiding all the jewelry with the two strips.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So whenever we needed a piece of jewelry, we had to take the door off the hinges, take the strip of wood, and take a piece of jewelry, and put the door back on the hinges.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So most of the valuables were hidden there, so they hardly found anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
